        <p>Suman Pokhrel is a contemporary Nepali poet known for his contributions to nationalist and social poetry. His poems often deal with themes of freedom, identity, and social change, reflecting the struggles of the common people. Pokhrel’s poetry is deeply rooted in the socio-political context of Nepal, where he addresses issues like social justice, nationalism, and human rights. His writing combines a personal touch with a collective vision, seeking to inspire the youth and promote societal transformation. Suman Pokhrel’s poetry has garnered recognition for its emotional depth and the relevance of its themes in today’s world.</p>
