        <p>Swami Vivekananda was not only a spiritual leader but also a poet whose works combined philosophy, spirituality, and classical poetry. His writings express a deep sense of devotion and respect for Indian culture, highlighting the importance of self-realization and social upliftment. His poetic style is marked by clarity of thought, rich imagery, and profound insights into human nature and the divine. Vivekananda’s classical poetry often focuses on themes of unity, strength, and spirituality, with a particular emphasis on the power of the individual to transform society. His work has inspired countless people to follow a path of self-discipline, strength, and service to humanity.</p>
